article.headline: Lamar 62, Cent. Arkansas 50
article.story: BEAUMONT, Texas (AP) -- James Davis scored 15 points and grabbed seven rebounds in Lamar's 62-50 win over Central Arkansas on Thursday night. Davis was 4-of-12 from the field and hit all seven of his free throw attempts. Lamar Sanders had his sixth double-double of the season, with 10 points and a team-high 18 rebounds. Both teams struggled from the field. Lamar (8-10, 2-2, Southland) hit only 38 percent of their shots compared to 32 percent shooting by Central Arkansas (6-12, 1-4). The Cardinals, who led 29-23 at halftime, broke a 31-31 tie with 14:57 remaining and secured the victory with a 13-2 run. Durrell Nevels led the Bears with 11 points and nine rebounds. Frederick Campbell added 10 points.
